Write a program that takes an array of integers and counts how many of them are odd & even numbers.

Example
Input: {3, 2, 4, 7, 10}
Output: even : 16, odd : 10

import java.util.*;
class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {3, 2, 4, 7, 10};
        int n = arr.length;
        int sumEven=0,sumOdd=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(arr[i]%2==0){
                sumEven+=arr[i];
            } else {
                sumOdd+=arr[i];
            }
        }
        System.out.println("Sum of Even numbers: "+sumEven);
        System.out.println("Sum of Odd numbers: "+sumOdd);
    }
}
